Ask HN: What are you doing with ChatGPT
text:
Using ChatGPT has been the closest thing I have felt to magic using tech in a long time. I notice much of the conversation about it is being framed by the worst polarized discourses of the moment. I have so little interest in things that narrow thinking into black and white. There is soo many amazing things to explore with the state of art language models. I wonder what are the things HNsers are curious about or trying out that are getting lost in the noise?

for example I have been getting it to recreate classic art with HTML canvas, output it responses in homoglyphs, write useful bash system maintenance scripts in the style of Talk therapy for computers, draft outlines for things I need to write, and so on and so forth..
